cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.BIO, cs.CV

The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques to predict splice junctions on DNA sequences. This falls under the intersection of machine learning and bioinformatics, which is a popular research area in computer science. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, since the paper deals with biological data, it could also be categorized under cs.BIO (Bioinformatics) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) due to the image-like nature of DNA sequences.
